POL-260.description:
## Objective

Implement a plan generator that consumes a `RepoScanInventory` and produces a structured `AdoptionPlan` ŌĆö both as JSON (`.polaris/adoption-plan.json`) and human-readable Markdown (`.polaris/adoption-plan.md`).

## Scope

Create `src/cli/adopt-plan.ts` implementing `generateAdoptionPlan(inventory: RepoScanInventory): AdoptionPlan`.

### AdoptionPlan schema

```typescript
interface AdoptionPlan {
  plan_id: string;           // e.g. "adoption-2026-05-31T..."
  generated_at: string;
  repo_state: RepoScanInventory["repo_state"];
  approved: boolean;
  approved_at: string | null;
  dry_run: boolean;
  steps: AdoptionStep[];
  impact_summary: AdoptionImpact;
}

interface AdoptionStep {
  step_id: string;
  order: number;
  phase: "A" | "B" | "C";
  category: "provider-config" | "scaffold" | "smartdocs-migrate" | "cognition-generate" | "instruction-refactor" | "atlas-generate" | "ignore-rules" | "stage";
  action: "create" | "move" | "modify" | "skip" | "append";
  source_path?: string;
  dest_path?: string;
  description: string;
  destructive: boolean;
  requires_approval: boolean;
  estimated_risk: "low" | "medium" | "high";
  status: "pending" | "completed" | "skipped" | "failed";
  completed_at?: string;
  error?: string;
}

interface AdoptionImpact {
  files_to_create: number;
  files_to_move: number;
  files_to_modify: number;
  instruction_files_affected: number;
  smartdocs_candidates_moved: number;
  cognition_files_to_generate: number;
}
```

### Markdown output

The `.polaris/adoption-plan.md` must show:

* Impact summary table
* Grouped list of steps by phase (A/B/C)
* Each step: action, source ŌåÆ dest (if applicable), risk badge, requires-approval flag

### `--dry-run` support

When `--dry-run` is passed to `polaris init --adopt`, set `dry_run: true` on the plan and skip all Phase C writes after printing what would happen.

## Files to touch

* `src/cli/adopt-plan.ts` (new)
* `src/cli/init.ts` ŌĆö wire `generateAdoptionPlan()` into the `--adopt` path

## Depends on

[POL-257](https://linear.app/lsctech/issue/POL-257/analyze-define-polaris-init-and-repository-adoption-workflow) Child 2 (repo scanner).

POL-259.description:
## Objective

Implement a read-only repo scanner that produces a `RepoScanInventory` JSON file at `.polaris/adoption-inventory.json`. No files are moved or modified during the scan.

## Scope

Create `src/cli/adopt-scan.ts` implementing `scanRepo(): Promise<RepoScanInventory>`.

### RepoScanInventory schema

```typescript
interface RepoScanInventory {
  scan_date: string;
  repo_state: "empty" | "new" | "partial" | "existing" | "polaris-enabled";
  package_manager: "npm" | "yarn" | "pnpm" | "bun" | null;
  source_roots: string[];
  docs_roots: string[];
  test_commands: string[];
  build_commands: string[];
  package_scripts: Record<string, string>;
  generated_roots: string[];
  cache_roots: string[];
  fixture_roots: string[];
  agent_instruction_files: AgentInstructionFile[];
  existing_smartdocs_dirs: string[];
  architecture_notes: string[];
  likely_canonical_folders: string[];
  smartdocs_candidates: SmartDocsCandidate[];
  ignore_candidates: string[];
}

interface AgentInstructionFile {
  path: string;
  provider: "claude" | "openai" | "copilot" | "cursor" | "gemini" | "aider" | "unknown";
  size_bytes: number;
  has_polaris_delegation: boolean;
  recommendation: "preserve" | "migrate" | "thin-adapter";
  reason: string;
}

interface SmartDocsCandidate {
  path: string;
  kind: "doc" | "spec" | "decision" | "architecture" | "integration" | "unknown";
  suggested_destination: string;
  confidence: number;
  has_frontmatter: boolean;
  estimated_risk: "low" | "medium" | "high";
}
```

### Detection rules

* **package_manager**: check for `yarn.lock`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `bun.lockb`, `package-lock.json` in that priority order
* **agent_instruction_files**: scan for `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `.github/copilot-instructions.md`, `.cursorrules`, `.cursor/rules/**/*.md`, `.aider.conf.yml`, `AIDER.md`, `**/GEMINI.md`
* **generated_roots**: detect `dist/`, `.next/`, `build/`, `out/`, `.turbo/`, `coverage/`
* **SmartDocs candidates**: any `.md`/`.mdx` > 100 bytes not in generated/cache/fixture/node_modules/.git/smartdocs
* **likely_canonical_folders**: folders with Ōēź 3 source files, not in generated/cache/fixture roots

Write the result to `.polaris/adoption-inventory.json` (never overwrite an existing inventory without `--rescan` flag).

## Files to touch

* `src/cli/adopt-scan.ts` (new)
* `src/cli/init.ts` ŌĆö wire `scanRepo()` into the `--adopt` path

## Depends on

[POL-257](https://linear.app/lsctech/issue/POL-257/analyze-define-polaris-init-and-repository-adoption-workflow) Child 1 (repo state detection) ŌĆö scan only runs for `existing` state.
